FBIS4-40861 "drsov119_s_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-119 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 Georgia Russian Peacekeeping Troops Reduced in S. Ossetia Russian Peacekeeping Troops Reduced in S. Ossetia LD2006165094 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1430 GMT 20 Jun 94 LD2006165094 Tbilisi IBERIA Georgian BFN [Text] Tskhinvali 20 [dateline as received] -- Peacekeeping forces stationed in the Tskhinvali region have undergone changes. While up to 1,000 Russian airborne assault troops were stationed in the region in 1992, only 523 soldiers of a motor rifle battalion of the Russian Armed Forces are involved in the peacekeeping operations there at the moment. The commanders of the Russian peacekeeping forces have said that they cannot stay in the region permanently. Therefore, Ossetians and Georgians should find a common language promptly to ensure a political settlement the current conflict.
